name: Run with me
description: Holding hands the river runs through us, makes us feel one with the wind of this city almost like in a boat, more than a boat adrift we walk the wide meadow of our spring, the first time we escaped to another world: another world that is in us. Garlands and lilies disguised and perfumed us, you wanted to jump the cliff that separated you from the boring monotony of a static reality. We ran away and escaped, now we are one with the cosmos.
